The paper focuses on unsupervised feature learning for visual data, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The approach proposed in the paper involves leveraging self-supervision and clustering, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also evaluates its approach on large-scale datasets, which is a common theme in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
